Kitui Governor Julius Malombe has promised his competitors a humiliating defeat in the August 8 general election. He said the battle for Wiper ticket will be a walkover. &ldquo; I joined the race as an underdog in 2012 and I beat wealthy and influential opponents at the party primaries and in the general election in 2013,&rdquo; Malombe told journalists in Kitui on Wednesday.The governor was responding to questions from the media after he delivered his state of the county address at the Ithookwe Showground in the outskirts of Kitui town.He highlighted 4,353 tangible and intangible projects his administration has achieved in the past four years. Malombe said he will be reelected on the account of his development record.